OL,3,CConsultants narrowly reject pay rise
OL,4,Cin latest ballot on government offer
OL,6,Fin England have voted narrowly against
OL,7,Fa government offer aimed at ending
OL,8,Ftheir long-running pay dispute.
OL,10,FOver 23,000 British Medical
OL,11,FAssociation (BMA) consultants voted
OL,12,F51.1% against a 4.95% pay rise offer
OL,13,Ffollowing a month long referendum.
OL,15,F"The vote has shown that consultants
OL,16,Fdo not feel the current offer goes far
OL,17,Fenough to end the current dispute and
OL,18,Foffer a long-term solution to the
OL,19,Frecruitment and retention crisis for
OL,20,Fsenior doctors, Dr Vishal Sharma, BMA
OL,21,Fconsultants committee chair, said.
